WEBVTT

00:04.484 --> 00:05.754
Hey, Calvin.

00:05.779 --> 00:07.660
Any news about Malcolm's job interview?

00:07.685 --> 00:10.056
Eh, not yet. Haven't heard anything.

00:10.081 --> 00:11.291
Oh, my God, it is killing me.

00:11.316 --> 00:12.861
I couldn't sleep a wink last night.

00:13.469 --> 00:15.504
I know. I got your texts

00:15.529 --> 00:17.994
at 2:00, 3:00 and 4:00 a.m.

00:19.066 --> 00:21.087
Look, I'm trying not to
worry about it too much.

00:21.112 --> 00:23.288
Oh, yeah, totally, duh.

00:23.590 --> 00:25.488
What was I thinking?

00:25.548 --> 00:27.750
But it has got to be killing you.

00:28.541 --> 00:30.422
I mean, it is an epic
story to be the father

00:30.447 --> 00:33.056
of a son who almost
made it to the majors,

00:33.110 --> 00:35.553
only to suffer a career-ending injury

00:35.578 --> 00:38.366
and then be rudderless for years.

00:39.510 --> 00:40.989
But now he's back.

00:41.041 --> 00:42.555
He's ready to carve out a path,

00:42.580 --> 00:44.345
but who knows doing what?

00:45.543 --> 00:46.998
You know, I never actually thought

00:47.023 --> 00:48.868
I'd hear myself say this, but...

00:49.062 --> 00:51.070
Dave, can we just talk about you?

00:51.741 --> 00:54.352
Oh, y-yeah, totally. Of-of course.

00:54.377 --> 00:55.585
What about me? Well...

00:55.610 --> 00:57.459
I'm just so nervous about Malcolm!

00:58.405 --> 00:59.513
Look.

01:00.001 --> 01:01.653
This is his first interview in a while.

01:01.678 --> 01:03.027
We're not even sure
if he's gonna get it.

01:03.052 --> 01:05.952
So, when he gets here,
let's just play it cool.

01:05.977 --> 01:06.967
- Yeah.
- All right?

01:06.992 --> 01:09.168
- Hey, guys.
- Did you get it?

01:09.454 --> 01:11.192
Did you get it? Come on, now.
Spit it out, boy.

01:11.217 --> 01:12.558
Pop. I got the job.

01:12.583 --> 01:14.185
- Yeah! All right.
- Yes!

01:14.210 --> 01:15.254
- Okay.
- Come on...

01:15.279 --> 01:17.176
Here we go.

01:19.640 --> 01:21.739
- Dave, excuse me.
- Oh.

01:21.793 --> 01:23.365
Gosh. I'm-I'm sorry.

01:23.390 --> 01:25.716
- All right.
- All right.

01:30.310 --> 01:33.646
- Synced and corrected by martythecrazy -
- www.addic7ed.com -

01:34.908 --> 01:36.953
Hey, everybody. Listen to Malcolm.

01:37.274 --> 01:39.363
- Well, turns out...
- He got the job!

01:39.388 --> 01:42.736
Oh, my God! He got the job! Oh, baby!

01:42.761 --> 01:45.611
I am so proud of you. I
knew you could do it.

01:45.636 --> 01:47.425
Aw, thanks, Ma, I appreciate it.

01:47.450 --> 01:49.455
Yeah, man, congrats.

01:49.480 --> 01:51.405
Now you can pay me back
that 50 bucks you owe me.

01:51.453 --> 01:52.676
Man...

01:52.701 --> 01:54.297
But seriously, congrats.

01:54.322 --> 01:55.584
But seriously, 50 bucks.

01:55.609 --> 01:57.611
Get out of here, man.

01:57.933 --> 01:59.492
- This is big, Malcolm.
- Mm-hmm.

01:59.517 --> 02:01.291
I mean, you're putting
yourself back out there

02:01.316 --> 02:03.475
and years from now, you're
gonna look back on this day

02:03.500 --> 02:05.540
- as a turning point in your life.
- Mm-hmm.

02:05.565 --> 02:07.231
Look, I don't know, Pop,
y'all are making too big

02:07.256 --> 02:08.505
a deal out of this, man.

02:08.530 --> 02:10.628
I am selling TVs at
Powerhouse Electronics.

02:10.654 --> 02:12.779
I'm not pitching in the World Series.

02:12.804 --> 02:15.644
Look, son. I know this
is not your dream job.

02:15.669 --> 02:17.455
But it doesn't mean that this can't be

02:17.480 --> 02:19.856
a stepping stone to something real.

02:19.881 --> 02:22.275
I mean, with your smarts,
and your work ethic,

02:22.335 --> 02:23.779
in a couple years, you
could be working yourself

02:23.804 --> 02:25.223
up the corporate ladder.

02:25.248 --> 02:26.265
I don't know, Pop.

02:26.290 --> 02:27.918
I've never worked in sales before.

02:27.943 --> 02:29.292
Well, you're in luck.

02:29.419 --> 02:32.217
I mean, I've had my
auto shop for 30 years.

02:32.242 --> 02:35.311
I could teach you all
about the ABC's of sales.

02:35.549 --> 02:38.667
Always Be Calvin.

02:40.587 --> 02:41.782
You mean, be grouchy

02:41.807 --> 02:43.986
and always forget to put
the toilet seat down?

02:44.702 --> 02:46.182
N-No, babe.

02:46.207 --> 02:47.604
Be confident.

02:47.629 --> 02:48.955
- Be charming.
- Mm-hmm.

02:48.980 --> 02:51.156
And always make it about
the customer's needs.

02:51.181 --> 02:53.518
This customer

02:53.543 --> 02:55.517
really needs you to put
the toilet seat down.

02:57.385 --> 02:59.627
- Okay, babe.
- Okay.

03:00.173 --> 03:02.111
Look, I'm-a show you how
it's done, all right?

03:02.136 --> 03:02.915
- Marty.
- All right.

03:02.940 --> 03:04.333
- Huh?
- Pretend to be a customer.

03:04.358 --> 03:05.898
Oh, sure.

03:05.923 --> 03:08.175
Excuse me, sir. Do you work here?

03:08.200 --> 03:10.025
Why yes, I do.

03:12.650 --> 03:14.074
How can I help you?

03:14.099 --> 03:15.691
Oh, well, you may want to know

03:15.716 --> 03:16.939
that I was just in the bathroom

03:16.964 --> 03:19.239
and somebody left the toilet seat up.

03:23.103 --> 03:25.892
Well, perhaps you have a
question about televisions.

03:25.917 --> 03:28.530
As a matter of fact, I do.

03:28.555 --> 03:31.522
Does this model have
VGA and HDMI inputs?

03:31.547 --> 03:33.870
And can it handle both
NTSC and PAL frame rates?

03:33.895 --> 03:35.398
'Cause I don't want to
be region-locked on a 4K

03:35.423 --> 03:36.670
when 8Ks are right around the corner.

03:36.695 --> 03:38.882
You know what I'm saying, big dog?

03:40.055 --> 03:42.759
I'll handle this, bro. Why don't
you go check on them toilets.

03:46.247 --> 03:48.993
I love that we're
afternoon friends now.

03:49.018 --> 03:50.901
Yeah, yeah, I know,

03:50.926 --> 03:53.111
but when you said that we
would be day drinking,

03:53.136 --> 03:55.772
this is not exactly what I had in mind.

03:57.351 --> 04:00.634
Ooh, Gemma, this Earl Grey
tastes like Chardonnay.

04:00.659 --> 04:02.628
The tea cup makes me feel less guilty.

04:04.842 --> 04:07.107
So I see you guys got a piano.
Who plays?

04:07.242 --> 04:08.789
Grover started taking lessons,

04:08.814 --> 04:11.705
but he's not really that into it.
He doesn't like his teacher.

04:11.901 --> 04:14.055
See, there's your problem right there.

04:14.080 --> 04:17.922
When teaching piano,
you have to have fun.

04:22.310 --> 04:24.656
I didn't know you played.

04:24.681 --> 04:27.242
Yeah, I started when I
was about Grover's age.

04:27.267 --> 04:29.918
My mom was the church organist.
I used to sit next to her

04:29.943 --> 04:32.075
while she'd teach me how
to play gospel songs,

04:32.100 --> 04:34.338
but she would add curse
words in it to make it fun.

04:34.882 --> 04:38.819
Like "hell-elujah"?

04:39.344 --> 04:41.133
Gemma, that's blasphemous.

04:42.532 --> 04:45.210
Well, I hope Grover can be
as good as you someday.

04:45.235 --> 04:47.367
Do you know any fun piano teachers?

04:47.392 --> 04:49.466
Well, I know the most fun one of all...

04:49.639 --> 04:52.019
me.

04:52.821 --> 04:55.442
Oh, my God, that would be so great.

04:55.549 --> 04:57.231
But, are you sure it's
not an imposition?

04:57.256 --> 05:00.973
No, not at all. I'll put up with
a lot for 50 bucks an hour.

05:04.098 --> 05:08.004
Oh, man, look at the size of these TVs.

05:08.182 --> 05:09.401
I know.

05:09.426 --> 05:12.366
My first TV, the screen was this big.

05:12.391 --> 05:15.013
- My first TV was black and white.
- Huh.

05:15.038 --> 05:16.910
Kind of like you and me.

05:17.543 --> 05:20.029
Yeah, except I can't turn you off.

05:23.293 --> 05:24.897
What are you guys doing here?

05:24.922 --> 05:27.038
Well, your dad just wanted
to see you in action.

05:27.063 --> 05:28.669
Yeah, and I was halfway
down the driveway

05:28.694 --> 05:31.384
when Dave jumped in
the back of my truck.

05:31.906 --> 05:34.127
Well, I appreciate you guys
coming out to support me,

05:34.152 --> 05:35.865
but, uh, I'm on the clock.

05:35.890 --> 05:39.346
Oh, look how professional he is.

05:39.755 --> 05:43.449
Yeah, got his shirt all
tucked in and his khakis.

05:45.384 --> 05:48.011
Hi there. Are you gentlemen
being taken care of?

05:48.036 --> 05:49.496
Are you kidding?

05:49.737 --> 05:53.165
This is the most impressive
salesman I've ever met.

05:53.190 --> 05:54.899
I mean, tell me the truth,

05:54.924 --> 05:57.849
how many times has he been
employee of the month?

05:58.208 --> 06:00.443
Uh, well, actually,
this is his first day.

06:00.468 --> 06:02.911
- What?
- What?

06:03.186 --> 06:05.843
Uh-uh. Uh-uh.

06:05.868 --> 06:09.151
Well, you know, you have
one heck of a salesman

06:09.176 --> 06:10.737
here in, uh...

06:11.523 --> 06:13.412
- Malcolm.
- Yeah.

06:13.445 --> 06:16.192
Let me guess, these are your dads?

06:17.521 --> 06:19.665
Yup. They sure are.

06:19.873 --> 06:23.261
Oh, no, we are not. I'm his dad.

06:23.286 --> 06:26.679
And I'm his neighbor,
but we're best friends.

06:30.083 --> 06:31.977
Okay, well, if you don't mind,

06:32.002 --> 06:33.831
there's a lady over there
who's actually interested

06:33.856 --> 06:36.966
- in buying something.
- Oh, please.

06:38.656 --> 06:40.904
Can you believe that guy

06:40.929 --> 06:43.062
actually thought we were a couple?

06:43.571 --> 06:45.833
Please, you could do worse.

06:49.404 --> 06:52.272
Okay, Grover, I guarantee
you this piano lesson

06:52.297 --> 06:54.087
is gonna be a lot more fun.

06:54.387 --> 06:55.867
How do you know?

06:55.892 --> 06:57.851
Because I've already had my tea.

06:59.148 --> 07:00.497
Now, the first step

07:00.541 --> 07:02.497
is to visualize your audience.

07:03.007 --> 07:04.227
I like to imagine

07:04.252 --> 07:06.509
that I'm walking on stage

07:06.791 --> 07:08.959
at the Apollo Theater.

07:10.200 --> 07:12.340
Oh, oh, thank you.

07:12.691 --> 07:15.074
Oh, thank you.

07:15.118 --> 07:17.300
Oh, hello.

07:17.941 --> 07:21.129
- Who are you waving at?
- Quincy Jones.

07:21.539 --> 07:24.281
- Who's that?
- Just a guy I used to date.

07:24.693 --> 07:26.632
Okay, now-now, come on, show me

07:26.657 --> 07:28.704
how you're gonna walk onto the stage.

07:32.011 --> 07:33.614
Hi, Mom.

07:34.117 --> 07:37.233
Oh, come on, Grove, that's all you got?

07:37.258 --> 07:38.907
Listen, these imaginary people

07:38.932 --> 07:41.174
paid a lot of money to come see you.

07:41.199 --> 07:43.826
Now strut your stuff, man. Come on.

07:44.807 --> 07:46.331
Uh-huh, okay.

07:46.356 --> 07:47.749
That's good.

07:48.412 --> 07:50.838
Okay. Get it.

07:50.863 --> 07:52.542
Oh, okay.

07:53.485 --> 07:55.969
All right, all right.

07:56.374 --> 07:59.667
Little rock star, you haven't
dropped the album as of yet.

08:00.169 --> 08:03.477
Now, most teachers teach
you how to play music.

08:03.502 --> 08:05.789
I'm gonna teach you how to feel music.

08:06.013 --> 08:07.873
Tell me how this makes you feel.

08:13.913 --> 08:16.572
- Scared.
- Mm.

08:16.597 --> 08:19.267
Like getting your credit
ran at a furniture store.

08:21.604 --> 08:23.480
Now how about this?

08:27.402 --> 08:29.576
- Happy?
- Oh!

08:29.601 --> 08:30.540
Like getting your credit approved,

08:30.565 --> 08:32.061
now you can get that waterbed!

08:34.624 --> 08:37.672
Can I just go back to
waving at my fans now?

08:37.883 --> 08:39.677
Yeah, but they're not
gonna cheer you on

08:39.702 --> 08:41.782
unless you play something, baby.

08:41.914 --> 08:43.735
- You're right.
- Yeah.

08:43.760 --> 08:46.499
Good thing our piano
has this demo button.

08:53.901 --> 08:58.182
Okay, mama's gonna need some more tea.
I'll be back.

09:00.758 --> 09:02.367
Hey, Trevor, you wanted to see me?

09:02.392 --> 09:03.797
Yeah, come on in.

09:03.822 --> 09:07.328
I was looking over the receipts,
and you sold four TVs today?

09:07.551 --> 09:08.864
Is that a good thing?

09:08.889 --> 09:10.766
Yeah, yeah, four TVs is great.

09:10.791 --> 09:13.353
Thank God. Man, I thought
I was in trouble.

09:13.378 --> 09:14.848
Oh, you are.

09:16.053 --> 09:18.736
Does it have something to
do with one of my two dads?

09:18.761 --> 09:21.141
Malcolm, it's great
that you sold four TVs,

09:21.166 --> 09:23.517
but we make our real
money on peripherals.

09:23.542 --> 09:26.814
You know, cables, warranties,
home installations.

09:26.839 --> 09:29.136
Yeah, I offered that to
all of my customers,

09:29.161 --> 09:30.554
but nobody was interested.

09:30.579 --> 09:33.245
Then you have to convince
people that they need them.

09:33.270 --> 09:35.666
Like that little old lady
you sold to earlier.

09:35.691 --> 09:37.931
If you had told her she
needed a warranty,

09:37.956 --> 09:39.089
she would've bought it.

09:39.114 --> 09:42.659
She was 80 years old, man. She
didn't need a 15-year warranty.

09:44.234 --> 09:47.304
Then why didn't you sign her up
for our in-store credit card?

09:47.329 --> 09:48.612
With 18% interest?

09:48.637 --> 09:50.866
Exactly. See, that's how
we really get them.

09:51.755 --> 09:54.056
Now go back out there
and make me proud.

09:54.081 --> 09:56.784
Oh, and push the 65-inch Hamagakis.

09:56.809 --> 09:58.906
They're about to be
recalled for exploding.

09:59.339 --> 10:02.024
Hey, whoa, whoa, whoa, Trevor,
I don't think I'm comfortable

10:02.049 --> 10:04.101
selling people stuff
they don't need, man,

10:04.204 --> 10:06.514
or that should come with
a fire extinguisher.

10:07.062 --> 10:09.274
Okay, got it. Totally understand.

10:09.360 --> 10:11.187
- Cool.
- You're fired.

10:11.212 --> 10:12.680
What?

10:12.820 --> 10:15.536
Look, man, clearly you're a good guy.

10:15.561 --> 10:17.733
If I knew that, I
wouldn't have hired you.

10:18.058 --> 10:20.240
Hold on, let's not be
too hasty, all right.

10:20.265 --> 10:23.124
I am not such a good guy.
I can do much worse.

10:23.391 --> 10:26.371
Mm, nah, man, not buying it. I
feel like you're lying to me,

10:26.396 --> 10:28.499
which is good, but too late.

10:29.609 --> 10:31.163
All right, fine.

10:31.206 --> 10:33.801
But I hope one of them Hamagakis
blows up in your face.

10:33.837 --> 10:35.268
No, you don't.

10:35.293 --> 10:37.286
Damn, you're right. I don't.

