contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

10:48.647 --> 10:50.954
Congratulations! Congratulations!

10:51.041 --> 10:53.915
You did it!

11:00.976 --> 11:02.478
Sorry about that.

11:02.595 --> 11:05.204
Probably should've thrown
that from farther away.

11:06.765 --> 11:08.352
Uh, wow, guys.

11:08.377 --> 11:10.104
You shouldn't have.

11:10.129 --> 11:11.810
You really shouldn't have.

11:12.499 --> 11:13.849
Yeah, man. I agree.

11:13.874 --> 11:15.384
It's just your first day.
And some of us

11:15.409 --> 11:17.304
have been employed for years, you know,

11:17.329 --> 11:19.760
as a rocket scientist.

11:20.471 --> 11:22.547
Have you ever sold anybody a rocket?

11:22.931 --> 11:25.038
Daddy, that's not how it works, man.

11:27.450 --> 11:29.582
We're just so happy for you.

11:29.607 --> 11:31.406
Yeah. Way to go, Malcolm.

11:31.431 --> 11:32.985
- Oh.
- Aw.

11:33.316 --> 11:35.062
Hey, thanks, little man.

11:35.087 --> 11:38.020
Son, you know I've been hard on you

11:38.045 --> 11:39.805
these last couple years, but...

11:39.830 --> 11:41.693
seeing you at work today,

11:41.718 --> 11:43.357
I'm proud of you, son.

11:44.368 --> 11:46.110
So, how was your first day?

11:46.301 --> 11:47.781
It was, um...

11:47.806 --> 11:48.984
unbelievable.

11:49.009 --> 11:50.538
Yeah, it was!

11:50.563 --> 11:52.475
All right!

11:58.280 --> 12:01.239
Come on, son. Everybody wants
to hear about your day.

12:01.283 --> 12:03.067
Um, you know, Pop, I, um...

12:03.110 --> 12:05.156
I sold some stuff, people
bought some stuff,

12:05.200 --> 12:08.242
and then I talked to my boss
about my future at the company.

12:08.472 --> 12:10.345
See, that's what I'm
talking about right there.

12:10.370 --> 12:11.325
See?

12:11.350 --> 12:12.826
Does anybody want to hear about my day?

12:13.056 --> 12:15.806
Today, my satellite
discovered a new supernova.

12:15.831 --> 12:17.175
Okay, not now, Marty. Listen,

12:17.200 --> 12:18.487
um...

12:18.847 --> 12:21.066
so, did you use any of my techniques?

12:21.091 --> 12:23.050
Uh, every single one of 'em, Pop.

12:23.075 --> 12:24.501
That's my boy right there.

12:24.526 --> 12:26.262
Just sayin',

12:26.287 --> 12:28.226
I am also your boy.

12:29.041 --> 12:30.421
So, did you

12:30.446 --> 12:32.418
use any of my techniques today?

12:33.037 --> 12:35.245
Well, I repositioned a
telemetry transponder

12:35.270 --> 12:37.011
from 60 million miles away.

12:37.303 --> 12:38.969
So all I'm hearing is "no."

12:42.324 --> 12:44.952
So, Grover said his piano
lesson went great.

12:44.977 --> 12:47.067
Ah. Yeah, he danced for five minutes,

12:47.092 --> 12:49.266
gave me his autograph, and then quit.

12:49.636 --> 12:51.290
What? He quit?

12:51.315 --> 12:52.830
Yeah. He dropped the mic,

12:52.855 --> 12:54.813
threw two fingers to the sky, and said,

12:54.857 --> 12:57.786
"Peace out, Pasadena! Grover
has left the building!"

12:58.534 --> 13:00.824
No, he can't quit.

13:00.849 --> 13:02.448
I stopped taking lessons
when I was his age,

13:02.473 --> 13:04.689
and I've regretted it ever since.

13:04.714 --> 13:06.766
Oh, wow. I didn't know
you wanted to play.

13:06.946 --> 13:09.340
Yeah.

13:09.365 --> 13:12.176
I have this fantasy where
I'm at a boring party,

13:12.201 --> 13:14.282
but there's a piano across the room.

13:14.307 --> 13:15.497
The crowd parts.

13:15.522 --> 13:16.994
I float over to it

13:17.019 --> 13:19.093
and start tickling those ivories.

13:19.118 --> 13:20.424
Next thing you know,

13:20.449 --> 13:22.286
there's a crowd gathered
around me making requests.

13:22.311 --> 13:24.052
And for some reason, Brad
Pitt is sitting next to me

13:24.077 --> 13:25.784
with his shirt off.

13:27.575 --> 13:29.312
So, you're making Grover take lessons

13:29.337 --> 13:31.912
because you regret giving it up.

13:32.797 --> 13:34.578
Well, yeah.

13:35.820 --> 13:37.981
Isn't living vicariously
through our kids

13:38.006 --> 13:40.344
half the reason why we have
them in the first place?

13:40.946 --> 13:42.611
Why don't you stop forcing Grover

13:42.636 --> 13:44.507
to do something he doesn't want to do

13:44.532 --> 13:46.732
and let me give you lessons instead?

13:46.757 --> 13:49.499
Oh, I don't know. It seems like
it's too late to start now.

13:49.524 --> 13:51.073
You're right. You're getting old.

13:51.098 --> 13:52.086
You might break a hip.

13:53.811 --> 13:55.735
Okay, fine. I'll give it a shot.

13:55.760 --> 13:57.424
Okay. Oh. And for the record,

13:57.449 --> 13:59.015
which Brad Pitt are we talking about?

13:59.040 --> 14:00.054
Fight ClubBrad.

14:00.079 --> 14:01.789
Ooh! That's a good Brad.

14:07.499 --> 14:09.017
Malcolm?

14:09.042 --> 14:11.208
Oh, hey, Dave. What's up?

14:11.233 --> 14:13.722
Hey, what are you doing here? I
thought you had work today...

14:15.200 --> 14:16.629
Oh, no.

14:16.654 --> 14:18.806
Look, Dave, I can explain, man.

14:18.831 --> 14:20.640
I just realized that if I had
been wearing a suit, too,

14:20.665 --> 14:23.327
we would look just like Men in Black.

14:25.385 --> 14:28.369
Yep, that is a missed
opportunity, Dave.

14:30.234 --> 14:31.987
Wait, are these job applications?

14:32.505 --> 14:35.180
Yeah. Look, the truth is,

14:35.439 --> 14:38.359
- I got fired yesterday, man.
- What? Why?

14:38.384 --> 14:40.400
Because they wanted me
to do some sleazy stuff

14:40.425 --> 14:42.107
that I wasn't comfortable with.

14:42.132 --> 14:43.602
Whoa.

14:45.000 --> 14:46.544
You mean, like, sex stuff?

14:47.176 --> 14:50.843
No, man. No, I mean, like,
ripping off old ladies.

14:50.868 --> 14:52.432
Oh... whoa.

14:52.457 --> 14:54.218
Well, that's bad, too.

14:57.535 --> 14:59.002
What'd your dad say?

14:59.027 --> 15:02.204
I haven't told him yet. I
mean, you saw him yesterday.

15:02.229 --> 15:04.856
He hasn't looked at me like that
since I was playing ball, man.

15:04.881 --> 15:06.648
He was in a pretty great mood.

15:06.673 --> 15:07.788
You know, after we left your store,

15:07.813 --> 15:09.528
all he wanted to do was
hang out together.

15:10.577 --> 15:12.420
We even split a giant pretzel.

15:13.058 --> 15:14.953
Wait, he split one with you?

15:14.978 --> 15:16.778
Not evenly.

15:17.803 --> 15:19.588
Yeah, well, I can't believe

15:19.613 --> 15:22.703
I finally landed a job and
get fired on my first day.

15:22.728 --> 15:24.131
That's humiliating.

15:24.156 --> 15:26.046
Well, you know what?
Maybe it's a good thing.

15:26.159 --> 15:28.113
You don't want to be stuck in a job

15:28.138 --> 15:29.864
that goes against your morals.

15:29.889 --> 15:31.661
Yeah, but I got to do something.

15:31.686 --> 15:35.994
You will. You're a smart,
hardworking good guy.

15:36.210 --> 15:37.756
A-And I'm not just saying that

15:37.781 --> 15:39.958
because I'm one of your two dads.

15:42.834 --> 15:45.272
Oh, hey, Calvin. You going somewhere?

15:45.297 --> 15:47.079
You know, I thought I'd
surprise Malcolm at work

15:47.104 --> 15:48.922
and take him out to lunch.

15:48.947 --> 15:50.967
Uh... d-don't do that.

15:52.055 --> 15:53.753
Why not?

15:53.778 --> 15:56.960
'Cause I was thinking, we had
such a nice time yesterday,

15:56.985 --> 16:01.553
maybe... maybe we should go
try a pretzel someplace else.

16:02.769 --> 16:05.641
You know, maybe do a little
Pasadena pretzel crawl.

16:07.100 --> 16:08.813
That's a hard pass, Dave.

16:09.064 --> 16:11.284
Hey, but, uh, bring me home one.

16:12.789 --> 16:15.581
All right, well, you got it.

16:15.606 --> 16:17.183
All right, well, you have a good time.

16:18.084 --> 16:20.609
Bye, now. We'll see you later.

16:23.860 --> 16:26.536
Uh... yeah, hey, M-Malcolm.
Yeah, it's Dave.

16:26.561 --> 16:28.882
Your dad is on his way to the store.

16:29.382 --> 16:31.514
No, no, I didn't tell him anything.

16:31.539 --> 16:33.056
I tried to stop him, but apparently,

16:33.081 --> 16:35.529
I made more of our pretzel
experience than he did,

16:35.554 --> 16:38.748
which totally backfired, 'cause
now I got to go get him one.

16:44.678 --> 16:46.467
Hey, Pop. Oh.

16:47.231 --> 16:48.406
Hey. Hey, there you are, man.

16:48.431 --> 16:49.780
I've been looking all over for you.

16:49.805 --> 16:51.087
Yeah, yeah, I was, uh...

16:51.112 --> 16:52.498
I was back there in a meeting.

16:52.523 --> 16:54.543
Mm, must be very important.

16:54.568 --> 16:57.118
- I see you got your suit on.
- Yeah.

16:57.143 --> 16:59.319
Uh... are they talking about
making you manager already?

16:59.344 --> 17:00.773
Oh, well, they definitely
said I wouldn't be

17:00.798 --> 17:02.538
in this position long.

17:03.999 --> 17:06.684
All right. Well, I just came
by to take you out to lunch.

17:06.709 --> 17:09.353
Oh, great, man, I'm starving.
Let's go right now.

17:09.377 --> 17:11.814
Oh, hold on. Don't you have to
check with your boss first?

17:11.839 --> 17:14.204
No, no. After our talk yesterday,

17:14.229 --> 17:16.515
I pretty much make up my own hours.

17:17.205 --> 17:20.156
Well, all right. That's good
right there. But you know what?

17:20.182 --> 17:21.373
Before we go,

17:21.397 --> 17:23.020
I've been thinking about
taking a look at some

17:23.045 --> 17:24.202
of these flat-screens right here,

17:24.227 --> 17:26.180
take advantage of that
employee discount.

17:26.204 --> 17:27.665
Oh, hey, Pop.

17:27.691 --> 17:29.497
Pop, you don't need a new TV, man.

17:29.522 --> 17:30.914
You know what you need?

17:30.939 --> 17:32.494
Uh... this.

17:32.638 --> 17:34.681
- A baby monitor?
- Yup. Yeah.

17:34.706 --> 17:36.441
I-It doesn't just monitor babies.

17:36.615 --> 17:38.392
You can listen to what
mom says about you

17:38.417 --> 17:40.798
when you're not around. Huh?

17:40.864 --> 17:43.330
It would be nice to hear
all those compliments.

17:43.355 --> 17:46.023
All right. That is great.

17:46.048 --> 17:47.369
I will ring it up for you

17:47.394 --> 17:50.173
and bring it home after my shift.
Let's go.

17:50.373 --> 17:51.983
Malcolm.

17:52.165 --> 17:53.697
What are you doing here?

17:53.721 --> 17:54.845
Uh, nothing. Uh, uh,

17:54.870 --> 17:56.720
just going out to lunch with my dad.

17:56.954 --> 17:58.322
H-Hold on. What,

17:58.347 --> 18:00.131
what does he mean by, "What
are you doing here?"

18:00.156 --> 18:02.533
I mean he doesn't work here anymore.

18:03.670 --> 18:05.047
What?

18:05.281 --> 18:06.930
I got fired yesterday, Pop.

18:06.955 --> 18:09.968
Fired? How is that even possible?

18:09.993 --> 18:11.516
I mean, how bad do you
have to be at something

18:11.541 --> 18:13.916
to get fired on your first damn day?

18:14.303 --> 18:15.959
Pretty bad, actually.

18:17.021 --> 18:19.100
He refused to do the job.

18:19.474 --> 18:20.904
Damn it, Malcolm.

18:20.947 --> 18:22.832
I mean, how can you
refuse to do anything?

18:22.857 --> 18:25.604
What I refused to do was
rip people off, Pop,

18:25.629 --> 18:27.750
and sell exploding TVs to old ladies.

18:27.775 --> 18:30.161
Hey, you could've sold
those TVs to anyone.

18:30.776 --> 18:35.046
Oh, h-hold on, now. You wanted
him to sell exploding TVs?

18:35.071 --> 18:38.224
Yes, but with an extended warranty.
I'm not a monster.

18:39.154 --> 18:42.152
All right, look, Pop, man, I
want you to be proud of me,

18:42.177 --> 18:44.290
but not if that means I
can't be proud of myself.

18:44.315 --> 18:46.370
Look, man, don't overthink it.

18:46.395 --> 18:48.816
Some people just aren't
cut out for success.

18:48.841 --> 18:51.747
Oh, oh, oh. Hold on, now.

18:51.839 --> 18:54.015
My son is gonna be a success.

18:54.040 --> 18:55.559
Because he has integrity

18:55.584 --> 18:57.277
and heart and principles,

18:57.302 --> 19:00.175
and that's why I know my son
is gonna rise to the top.

19:00.200 --> 19:03.206
He's not gonna be some
bottom-feeder like you.

19:04.884 --> 19:06.378
All right, whatever.

19:07.107 --> 19:09.738
I just came out of my office to chat up

19:09.763 --> 19:12.988
that hot pregnant lady I saw
on the security camera.

19:13.013 --> 19:14.554
Bye.

19:16.767 --> 19:18.537
Dude's a jackass.

19:19.053 --> 19:21.454
Yeah, look, Pop, I was gonna
tell you the truth, man,

19:21.479 --> 19:23.874
but I just wanted to
find another job first.

19:24.212 --> 19:25.689
Look, man,

19:25.714 --> 19:27.785
I know I put a lot of pressure on you,

19:27.810 --> 19:30.704
but you never have to lie to me
about doing the right thing.

19:31.277 --> 19:33.583
Cool. Thanks, Pop.

19:33.608 --> 19:36.041
All right. So how about
we get that lunch?

19:36.066 --> 19:38.222
Sounds good to me. Where we going?

19:38.403 --> 19:40.799
First restaurant we see
with a "help wanted" sign.

19:49.299 --> 19:50.882
How's it going, Mom?

19:50.907 --> 19:54.178
Uh, okay, but it's
harder than I thought.

19:54.203 --> 19:56.275
Maybe you should have some tea.

19:58.144 --> 20:00.364
Miss Tina says it makes
everything better.

20:02.267 --> 20:04.427
What else did Miss Tina teach you?

20:04.452 --> 20:06.734
Well, she taught me to always start

20:06.759 --> 20:08.344
by waving to your audience.

20:08.630 --> 20:10.442
Hey, Quincy.

20:11.909 --> 20:14.141
Now, let's start with a simple scale.

20:14.166 --> 20:15.545
Okay.

20:22.541 --> 20:25.138
Grover, that's really good.

20:25.163 --> 20:27.253
I thought you didn't
like playing piano.

20:27.328 --> 20:31.427
I didn't. But I think maybe
I like playing with you.

20:32.947 --> 20:36.121
Well, we could take lessons
from Miss Tina together.

20:36.146 --> 20:37.712
That sounds fun.

20:37.974 --> 20:40.361
But first, let's give
some love to our fans.

20:40.386 --> 20:41.588
Yeah.

20:45.765 --> 20:47.255
Who are you waving at?

20:47.280 --> 20:49.412
Oh, just this guy named Brad.

